Demonstrators also received the support of other prominent New York Democrats, such as Mayoral candidate Bill de Blasio, who said that “we must come together to support fast food workers so that they can achieve the fair reward for their work and economic prosperity that every New Yorker deserves!”
As the New York Times described it, it was the largest event of its kind in the history of the American fast food industry.
But only a few hundred people attended, although not all of them were fast food workers, who employ tens of thousands of people in New York.
Whether this event will become a spark that will ignite the flame of the mass movement is still unclear.
