Rather, our goal should be to feel comfortable when we are out of reach of the constant grinding of activity and technology.
Professor Eastwood agreed.
"We accuse her of having to be bored even more, but boredom is a painful, restless desire to be associated with something meaningful," he said.
What people are really looking for, he said, is a way to relax and enjoy your free time.
“In an environment where we’re constantly re-stimulated,” he said, “it’s hard to find ways to have fun when the noise goes off.”
